The All Progressives Congress (APC) has said the Edo State governor, Mr Godwin Obaseki, is now too desperate to get re-elected, even as it admonished him that his ambition is not worth the blood of any Edo citizen. This call was made by a former member, House of Representatives, and vice chairman, Communication and Publicity Committee of the APC national campaign council, Hon. Patrick Obahiagbon, flanked by the committee chairman, Prince John Mayaki, during a press conference yesterday in Abuja. He also raised the alarm over the alleged importation of political thugs from neighbouring states by the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), saying firearms are now being used freely in the state by thugs as if the arms are “political chewing gums”. LEADERSHIP Weekend recalls the PDP had earlier accused the APC of stoking violence with a view to getting the elections postponed in order to allow it more time to perfect plans to manipulate the process. Obahiagbon accused the PDP of using violence to intimidate the people in order to encourage voter apathy during the polls. “Let the whole world tell Gov. Godwin Obaseki that his second term ambition is not worth the blood and life of any Edo State citizen,” he said.